# Rule: Hybrid Feature Styling and State

## Styling Directives (Tailwind-First)

- Use Tailwind CSS as the default styling approach across the app.
- Prefer Tailwind classes for component styling, especially in Shadcn-based UI work.
- Only use SCSS when Tailwind is insufficient for the required behavior.
- SCSS fallback must be local CSS Modules (`*.module.scss`) and follow `@use`/`@forward` patterns.

## SCSS-Appropriate Cases

- Complex SVG styling requirements
- Advanced orientation/masking layouts
- Complex multi-step CSS animations

## State and API Placement

- Place global domains (auth, user profiles, sessions, app-wide config) in `src/shared/` or `src/core/`.
- Keep single-use APIs and highly localized state inside the owning feature directory.
- Do not centralize feature-only state or APIs prematurely.
